## Questionnaire backend alignment (Django)

- New accepted fields: `moods`, `moments`, `times`, `intensity`, `styles`, `noteLikes`, `noteDislikes`, `limit`.
- Legacy fields still accepted: `contexts`, `sweetness`, `freshness`, `strength`, `gender`, `avoid_very_sweet`, `avoid_oud`.
- Validation lives in `backend/api/serializers.py`.
- Mapping to tokens lives in `backend/matcher/bridge_config.py`; profile builder/penalties are in `backend/matcher/vectorizer.py`.
- Example request body (POST `/api/recommend/`):
```json
{
  "moods": ["fresh", "sweet"],
  "moments": ["daily", "evening"],
  "times": ["day"],
  "intensity": ["medium"],
  "styles": ["unisex"],
  "noteLikes": ["citrus", "woody"],
  "noteDislikes": ["sweet"],
  "limit": 8
}
```
- Behavior:
  - noteLikes expand to note/accord tokens
  - noteDislikes penalize perfumes sharing those note categories
  - moments/times add occasion bias; intensity/style add intensity/gender bias
  - legacy sliders still influence tokens
